    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-14T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Indonesia/3–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Baruch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d228fn1">Repeated in telegram 169, <gloss target="#t_Usgoc1"
                            >Usgoc</gloss> 336, March 15, 6 p. m., to Batavia.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-14T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 14, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>246. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 213, March 12 (<gloss
                        target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 625<note n="2" xml:id="d228fn2">Telegram
                        250, March 11, <ref target="#pg_315">p. 315</ref>, and footnote 1.</note>)
                    contained information of such importance from Dutch point of view that substance
                    thereof (mainly contained 5 numbered points), was communicated this afternoon
                    Lovink, in absence Stikker, London.</p>
                <p>Stressing major Dutch objection restoration Djocja, that chaos inevitable result,
                    Cochran view need for minimum number supplementary military police was pressed
                    in conjunction with Cochran statements <gloss target="#t_UNCFIN1">UNCFI</gloss>
                    would have responsibility seeing Djocja not become haven or concentration point
                    for armed forces. This statement, coupled with Cochran indication that
                    Republican leaders must be reasonable once restored Djocja and <gloss
                        target="#t_UNCFIN1">UNCFI</gloss> would consider its duty to insist thereon,
                    made obvious deep impression. On other hand, became clear that Dutch, including
                    Stikker in letter March 8 (paragraph 3), have been thinking in terms of Djocja
                    civil police and armed forces, both under Dutch.</p>
                <pb facs="0337" n="323" xml:id="pg_323"/>
                <p>Lovink advised Van Royen being instructed agree McNaughton proposal at <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baruch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
